HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 255
BY REPRESENTATIVES BEAULLIEU, BOUDREAUX, BRYANT, BUTLER, CARVER,
CHASSION, GLORIOSO, HEBERT, JACOB LANDRY, AND SPELL
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the students and faculty of the Lafayette Parish School
System for winning first place in the Louisiana Governor's Games Thirty-First
Annual Elementary State Championship Fitness Meet
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate the students and faculty of the Lafayette Parish School
3 System for their first place finish in the Louisiana Governor's Games Thirty-First
4 Annual Elementary State Championship Fitness Meet.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Governor's Games are the state's premier amateur
6 sporting event; and
7 WHEREAS, the Lafayette Parish School System finished first overall in the Thirty-
8 First annual Elementary State Championship Fitness Meet; and
9 WHEREAS, Lafayette secured first place by scoring a total of 2,479 points, which
10 outpaced the 2,459 points scored by second-place St. Tammany and the 2,428 points scored
11 by third-place Rapides; and
12 WHEREAS, the elementary fitness meet competition involves seven fitness-related
13 events: the fifty-yard dash, the shuttle run, pull-ups, the standing long-jump, curl-ups or
14 sit-ups, the six hundred-yard run, and the V-sit and reach; and
15 WHEREAS, the top two boys and girls from each parish compete in Alexandria
16 annually for the fitness title; and
17 WHEREAS, Lafayette's top performer, Tianna Franks, led the way with six hundred
18 forty-eight individual points; she and her teammates, Brennon Poullard, Amir Alsayed, and
19 Aubrey Porter, anchored their parish to victory; and
